Adds a value into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

Runs multiple commands by creating a remote shell and checking output against regular expressions

Inputs\:
host - Hostname or ip address.
port - port number for connecting to.
command - The commands to execute. This should be made up of 'send ' and 'expect ' statements separated by newlines.
username - Username to connect as.
password - Password of user. If using a private key file this will be used as the passphrase for the file.
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host (used by SSH).
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) Time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete. Also used as an authentication timeout.
protocol - The protocol used to connect. If not specified SSH is tried first, then Telnet is tried.
usernamePrompt - The prompt that when seen should send the username.
passwordPrompt - The prompt that when given should send the password.
newlineCharacters - The character sequence to send as the enter key being pressed after each 'send' statement as the send expect script is processed in the command input. Either '\r\n' '\n' '\r' or a comma delimited list of ASCII escape sequences.
characterSet - The characterSet name for stream encoding and decoding between the RAS and target machine. For example\: SJIS, EUC-JP, UTF-8.  By default it is UTF-8.

Responses\:
success - The command was executed successfully.
failure - The command could not be executed.

Extra Results\:
visualized - The output of the command in XML format.
STDOUT - The STDOUT of the command.
protocol - The protocol used to connect. SSH is tried first, then telnet is tried.

Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your NAS core. corePort - The port to connect to your NAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your NAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for the NAS core. corePassword - The password for the NAS user. id - The ID of the object to process. ip - The IP address of the network device. returnImmediately - A boolean value. ad900ba6-cb0b-4c05-9c13-72292db09f33.dc524943-6eee-448f-937e-80bdcd9b5c86.prompt=Enter a value for ip ad900ba6-cb0b-4c05-9c13-72292db09f33.description=
Demonstrates how to roll back a command on a Cisco router if the command makes the router unreachable.

Inputs\:
coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your NA core.
coreUsername - The username for the NA core.
corePassword - The password for the NA user.
host -The ip of your Cisco router.
username - The username for host.
password - The password for host.
enablePassword - To enabled mode password for host.
groupName - The name of the NA group containing the device.

Responses\:
success - The change made successfully.
failure - When something went wrong.
